    "§10 establishes that picking a single subsample causes the comparison between acc test and acc extra to be a coin flip.",
    "But is the result of the coin flip explained by the specific subsample that was drawn?",
    "If so, comparing models using a single subsample may not be so noisy, because the effect of pretraining on unlabeled test set text would be consistent across models.",
    "One way to answer this question is to measure the correlation between the evaluation bias of BERT and GPT-2 for each setting of m and n, and each of the 25 tasks.",
    "A positive correlation suggests that the subsample causes the evaluation bias."
  ],
